    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-09-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-09-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="527" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d527">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Pike</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 249.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                        of State, Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-09-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 4, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your very interesting despatch of the
                            16th ultimo, No. 173, informing me of the important matters which are
                            engaging the attention of the European <pb facs="0471" n="397" xml:id="pg_397"/> public, has been received, and I have, in reply,
                            to inform you that I have invited the attention of the Secretary of the
                            Treasury to that portion which relates to the financial situation in
                            Europe.</p>
                <p>Upon representations which have been received from the diplomatic agents
                            of the United States in Europe, the attention of the governors and
                            provisional governors of the several States has been called to the
                            reported progress of the cholera westward, and the adoption of such
                            measures as will prevent its introduction into the United States has
                            been recommenced.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James</hi> S. <hi rend="smallcaps">Pike,</hi>
                                    Esq.,<hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,&amp;c.,&amp;</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
